      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " الرَّجُلِ يَتَزَوَّجُ الْمُتْعَةَ أَ تُحْصِنُهُ قَالَ لَا إِنَّمَا ذَاكَ عَلَى الشَّيْ‏ءِ الدَّائِمِ عِنْدَهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, form Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hisham and Hafs Bin Al Bakhtary, from the one who mentioned, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> regarding the man who married the temporary marriage, would he be (classified as) married?’ He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘No. But rather that (being married) is upon the thing which is always with him’."
        ]
      }
